      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The recent form of CHRISSY EVE (8) may not leap off the page but she has been tackling stronger opposition at Wagga. Better placed and is well up to winning this with even luck from the back row. SOPHIES SCOOTER (7) recorded her second win from the past four outings when she found the lead and kept going to score by 2.2 metres at Leeton last start. Has won at this circuit and distance before. Drawn to enjoy a cosy run and if she gets the gaps could feature again. OUR ULTIMATE BONNY (2) has had some tough barriers since winning at Wagga last month. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a good run and she could show her best from there. ALTA BAYAMO (9) draws on the back row again but is open to improvement following a respectable third when resuming at Echuca. The ace draw could see ARMA THE GREAT (1) find the form that saw him score three back at Wagga.",
